The `copyBtn` listener sets `btn.textContent = "Copied"` **before** awaiting `navigator.clipboard.writeText()`. This means the button shows "Copied" immediately, even before the clipboard write succeeds or fails. If the clipboard API is blocked (e.g., on `file://` URLs), the user sees "Copied" for 1.5 seconds despite no data being copied.

**Suggestion:** Move the button text update inside the success path:
```javascript
$("copyBtn").addEventListener("click", async () => {
  try {
    await navigator.clipboard.writeText(JSON.stringify(buildConfig(), null, 2));
    const btn = $("copyBtn");
    const original = btn.textContent;
    btn.textContent = "Copied";
    setTimeout(() => (btn.textContent = original), 1500);
  } catch (_) {
    // Clipboard API may be blocked on file:// - consider showing "Copy failed" or using download fallback
  }
});
```

